ude will reflect each one in a follow-up commit.\n3. **MEDIUM findings** (MEDIUM-N): may be deferred via `decisions.md` ADR addendum, but state your recommendation.\n4. **LOW findings** (LOW-N): optional / nit / blockers.md candidates.\n5. **META** — anything systemic about the implementation approach, the SH-FOLLOWUP-1/SH-FOLLOWUP-2 judgement calls, or the scope of the M10-0 gate. In particular, evaluate:\n   - **META-1**: does this 3-commit set close the M10-0 go/no-go gate that META-1 of your 13th review (PR #170) flagged? If not, what is still missing?\n   - **META-2**: did the SH-FOLLOWUP-1 decision (keep `deny()` returning exit 0 + JSON, do not migrate to exit 2) regress any property of the Codex hook protocol you can verify against the upstream Codex docs?\n   - **META-3**: SH-FOLLOWUP-2 routed the SH-1 print backstop through `ruff check --select T201` instead of a literal grep. Confirm whether the `inference/ollama_adapter.py:145` raw `print()` is actually a legitimate gap (and thus the ruff-equivalent design is fine) or a real existing-violation we should burn down here.\n6. **Fact-check sheet** — restate any of the commands in the sheet above whose output you re-ran or any new ones you ran independently. Quote the actual output.\n\n## Scope-specific risks for you to evaluate\n\n- **SH-2 startup gate**: is the `RuntimeError` on `host=0.0.0.0 + all gates off` going to break the user's existing daily LAN workflow in a way the runbook (`docs/development-guidelines.md`) does not adequately surface? Note: memory `feedback_crlf_canonical_for_md5.md` and the SH-2 ADR explicitly preserve `host=0.0.0.0` default; the gate's contract is \"you must opt into ONE protection\".\n- **SH-2 reserve_slot atomicity**: `len(self._queues) >= self._max_sessions` followed by `self._queues[session_id] = queue` is atomic relative to other event-loop callers because Python's asyncio is single-threaded, but verify the pre-accept fast-path and the in-loop authoritative `reserve_slot` are wired correctly so the race window (between pre-check and reserve) is closed by `_send_error` + close 1013, not by a silent allow.\n- **SH-1 shell regex coverage**: the 7 regex patterns in `shell_write_targets` aim for the 5 red-team cases plus generic `>`/`>>` redirects with file extensions. Identify obvious bypasses I missed (e.g., `python -c \"exec(...)\"` indirection, base64-encoded payloads, `xargs` chains).\n- **SH-1 CI gate behaviour on PRs from forks**: `policy-grep-gate` uses `fetch-depth: 0` and `git diff origin/main...HEAD`. Does this work for fork PRs where `origin` resolves to the fork? Check the GitHub Actions behaviour.\n- **MEDIUM logger.warning** placement: I added the log inside the existing `if self._envelopes.maxsize > 0 and self._envelopes.full()` branch, after the count was bumped but before the warning ErrorMsg was enqueued. Confirm there is no path where the count is bumped but the log is skipped, or vice versa.\n- **MEDIUM test coverage**: `test_consume_result_path_uses_drop_oldest_helper` calls the private `_enqueue_with_drop_oldest` directly rather than constructing a `CycleResult` and driving `_consume_result`. Is the shared-helper proof sufficient, or do you want a higher-fidelity test that exercises the full envelope loop?\n\n## Constraints (must be preserved)\n\n- `data/eval/golden/` / `src/erre_sandbox/evidence/` unchanged (verified empty in fact-check sheet)\n- `SCHEMA_VERSION = \"0.10.0-m7h\"` unchanged (verified)\n- No new `ControlEnvelope` types; the gateway uses existing `ErrorMsg.code` with new string value `\"session_cap_exceeded\"` (lifecycle scope) — consistent with SH-5's `\"runtime_backlog_overflow\"`\n- `require_token=False` default (back-compat)\n- `host=0.0.0.0` default preserved\n- `idea_judgement*.md` / `data/eval/golden/_checksums_mac_received.txt` deliberately excluded from these commits\n\n## Self-tests to run if you have shell\n\n```bash\nuv run ruff check src tests\nuv run ruff format --check src tests\nuv run mypy src\nuv run pytest -q -m \"not godot and not eval and not spike and not training and not inference\"\nuv run pytest tests/test_integration/test_gateway.py tests/test_codex_hooks tests/test_world/test_runtime_lifecycle.py -q\n\n# Codex hook smoke (SH-FOLLOWUP-1 JSON match form)\necho '{\"tool\":\"exec_command\",\"tool_input\":{\"command\":\"sed -i s/x/y/ src/erre_sandbox/x.py\"}}' \\\n  | uv run python .codex/hooks/pre_tool_use_policy.py \\\n  | jq -e '.hookSpecificOutput.permissionDecision == \"deny\"'\n```\n\nReturn your review as plain text starting with the executive verdict. Brevity is welcome; depth is welcome too — pick what serves the gate decision.\n","images":[],"local_images":[],"text_elements":[]}}
/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/15/rollout-2026-05-15T18-02-57-019e2adf-e667-7241-b4b7-edcb4561a395.jsonl:66:{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T09:04:00.367Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_Av8Gmzyf2oUCw2b8K9GLEpou","output":"Chunk ID: 76c229\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2429\nOutput:\n     1\t#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     3\t\n     4\timport re\n     5\tfrom pathlib import Path\n     6\tfrom typing import Any\n     7\t\n     8\tfrom _erre_common import emit_json, latest_task, read_payload, relative_path, repo_root, task_status\n     9\t\n    10\tIMPL_PREFIX = \"src/erre_sandbox/\"\n    11\t\n    12\t# SH-1 — shell-write detection. These regex patterns flag the canonical\n    13\t# ways a shell command can write to a file on disk so the hook can reject\n    14\t# any write that targets ``src/erre_sandbox/``. The matcher in\n    15\t# ``.codex/hooks.json`` widens to ``exec_command|Bash`` so this path now\n    16\t# fires for tool calls that previously bypassed the ``apply_patch|Edit|\n    17\t# Write`` filter. False negatives are acceptable since the CI\n    18\t# ``policy-grep-gate`` job is a second backstop; false positives only\n    19\t# fire on shell commands that target ``src/erre_sandbox/`` so the user\n    20\t# can re-issue via Edit/Write.\n    21\tSHELL_WRITE_PATTERNS: list[re.Pattern[str]] = [\n    22\t    # sed -i / gsed -i [-i.bak] [-e ...] PATH (in-place edit)\n    23\t    re.compile(\n    24\t        r\"\\b(?:g?sed)\\s+-i(?:\\s+(?:''|\\.\\w+))?\"\n    25\t        r\"(?:[^|;]*?\\s+-e\\s+(?:'[^']*'|\\\"[^\\\"]*\\\"|\\S+))?\"\n    26\t        r\"[^|;]*?\\s(?P<path>[\\w./-]+\\.\\w+)\\b\",\n    27\t    ),\n    28\t    # perl -pi / -pie -e ... PATH\n    29\t    re.compile(\n    30\t        r\"\\bperl\\s+-pi(?:e)?(?:[^|;]*?\\s+-e\\s+(?:'[^']*'|\\\"[^\\\"]*\\\"))?\"\n    31\t        r\"[^|;]*?\\s(?P<path>[\\w./-]+\\.\\w+)\\b\",\n    32\t    ),\n    33\t    # tee [-a] PATH (write or append)\n    34\t    re.compile(r\"\\btee\\b(?:\\s+-a)?\\s+(?P<path>[\\w./-]+\\.\\w+)\\b\"),\n    35\t    # cat > PATH << EOF (heredoc redirect)\n    36\t    re.compile(r\"\\bcat\\s+>>?\\s*(?P<path>[\\w./-]+\\.\\w+)\\s*<<\"),\n    37\t    # Generic shell redirect ``> PATH.ext`` or ``>> PATH.ext`` — catches\n    38\t    # echo / printf / dd / generic pipelines. The ``\\.\\w+`` tail keeps\n    39\t    # this from matching ``> /dev/null`` and the like.\n    40\t    re.compile(r\"(?<![<>])>>?\\s*(?P<path>[\\w./-]+\\.\\w+)\\b\"),\n    41\t    # python -c \"...open('PATH', 'w'|'a'|'wb'|'ab'...).write(...)...\"\n    42\t    re.compile(\n    43\t        r\"python3?\\s+-c\\s+['\\\"][^'\\\"]*?open\\s*\\(\\s*\"\n    44\t        r\"['\\\"](?P<path>[^'\\\"]+)['\\\"]\\s*,\\s*['\\\"][wa]b?\\+?\",\n    45\t    ),\n    46\t    # python -c \"...Path('PATH').write_(text|bytes)...\"\n    47\t    re.compile(\n    48\t        r\"python3?\\s+-c\\s+['\\\"][^'\\\"]*?Path\\s*\\(\\s*\"\n    49\t        r\"['\\\"](?P<path>[^'\\\"]+)['\\\"]\\s*\\)\\s*\\.\\s*write_(?:text|bytes)\",\n    50\t    ),\n    51\t]\n    52\t\n    53\t\n    54\tdef shell_write_targets(command: str) -> list[str]:\n    55\t    \"\"\"Return paths a shell command would write to (best-effort regex).\n    56\t\n    57\t    The hook treats any returned path that lies under ``IMPL_PREFIX`` as\n    58\t    a violation (see :func:`main`). Returning a path outside ``IMPL_PREFIX``\n    59\t    is harmless because :func:`is_impl_path` filters it out at the call\n    60\t    site; the caller never reads content from this helper, only the path\n    61\t    list.\n    62\t    \"\"\"\n    63\t    targets: list[str] = []\n    64\t    seen: set[str] = set()\n    65\t    for pattern in SHELL_WRITE_PATTERNS:\n    66\t        for match in pattern.finditer(command):\n    67\t            path = match.group(\"path\")\n    68\t            if path and path not in seen:\n    69\t                seen.add(path)\n    70\t                targets.append(path)\n    71\t    return targets\n    72\t\n    73\t\n    74\tBANNED_PATTERNS: list[tuple[str, re.Pattern[str]]] = [\n    75\t    (\n    76\t        \"cloud LLM API imports are forbidden in src/erre_sandbox\",\n    77\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*(?:import\\s+(?:openai|anthropic)\\b|from\\s+(?:openai|anthropic)\\b)\"),\n    78\t    ),\n    79\t    (\n    80\t        \"bpy imports are forbidden in src/erre_sandbox because Blender/GPL code is isolated\",\n    81\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*(?:import\\s+bpy\\b|from\\s+bpy\\b)\"),\n    82\t    ),\n    83\t    (\n    84\t        \"print() is forbidden in src/erre_sandbox; use logging instead\",\n    85\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*print\\s*\\(\"),\n    86\t    ),\n    87\t]\n    88\t\n    89\t\n    90\tdef deny(reason: str) -> int:\n    91\t    emit_json(\n    92\t        {\n    93\t            \"hookSpecificOutput\": {\n    94\t                \"hookEventName\": \"PreToolUse\",\n    95\t                \"permissionDecision\": \"deny\",\n    96\t                \"permissionDecisionReason\": reason,\n    97\t            }\n    98\t        }\n    99\t    )\n   100\t    return 0\n   101\t\n   102\t\n   103\tdef patch_targets(command: str) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n   104\t    targets: dict[str, list[str]] = {}\n   105\t    current: str | None = None\n   106\t    for line in command.splitlines():\n   107\t        for marker in (\"*** Add File: \", \"*** Update File: \", \"*** Delete File: \"):\n   108\t            if line.startswith(marker):\n   109\t                current = line[len(marker) :].strip()\n   110\t                targets.setdefault(current, [])\n   111\t                break\n   112\t        else:\n   113\t            if current and line.startswith(\"+\") and not line.startswith(\"+++\"):\n   114\t                targets[current].append(line[1:])\n   115\t    return targets\n   116\t\n   117\t\n   118\tdef direct_targets(tool_input: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n   119\t    result: dict[str, list[str]] = {}\n   120\t    for key in (\"file_path\", \"path\"):\n   121\t        value = tool_input.get(key)\n   122\t        if isinstance(value, str) and value:\n   123\t            content = tool_input.get(\"new_string\") or tool_input.get(\"content\") or \"\"\n   124\t            if isinstance(content, str):\n   125\t                result[value] = content.splitlines()\n   126\t    edits = tool_input.get(\"edits\")\n   127\t    target = tool_input.get(\"file_path\") or tool_input.get(\"path\")\n   128\t    if isinstance(edits, list) and isinstance(target, str):\n   129\t        lines: list[str] = []\n   130\t        for edit in edits:\n   131\t            if isinstance(edit, dict) and isinstance(edit.get(\"new_string\"), str):\n   132\t                lines.extend(edit[\"new_string\"].splitlines())\n   133\t        result[target] = lines\n   134\t    return result\n   135\t\n   136\t\n   137\tdef target_map(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n   138\t    tool_input = payload.get(\"tool_input\")\n   139\t    if not isinstance(tool_input, dict):\n   140\t        return {}\n   141\t    command = tool_input.get(\"command\")\n   142\t    if isinstance(command, str) and \"*** Begin Patch\" in command:\n   143\t        return patch_targets(command)\n   144\t    return direct_targets(tool_input)\n   145\t\n   146\t\n   147\tdef is_impl_path(path: str) -> bool:\n   148\t    return path.startswith(IMPL_PREFIX)\n   149\t\n   150\t\n   151\tdef check_banned(path: str, lines: list[str]) -> str | None:\n   152\t    if not path.endswith(\".py\") or not is_impl_path(path):\n   153\t        return None\n   154\t    for line in lines:\n   155\t        for label, pattern in BANNED_PATTERNS:\n   156\t            if pattern.search(line):\n   157\t                return f\"{label}: {path}: {line.strip()}\"\n   158\t    return None\n   159\t\n   160\t\n   161\tdef main() -> int:\n   162\t    payload = read_payload()\n   163\t    root = repo_root(payload)\n   164\t    # SH-1: shell-write bypass guard. The PreToolUse matcher in\n   165\t    # ``.codex/hooks.json`` widens to ``exec_command|Bash`` so this branch\n   166\t    # is now reachable for shell tool calls. Any shell command that writes\n   167\t    # into ``src/erre_sandbox/`` is rejected regardless of the would-be\n   168\t    # content — the change must go through Edit/Write/apply_patch so the\n   169\t    # same policy guards (banned imports, ``.steering`` completeness,\n   170\t    # diff review trail) apply uniformly.\n   171\t    tool_input = payload.get(\"tool_input\")\n   172\t    if isinstance(tool_input, dict):\n   173\t        command = tool_input.get(\"command\")\n   174\t        if isinstance(command, str) and \"*** Begin Patch\" not in command:\n   175\t            impl_shell_targets: list[str] = []\n   176\t            for raw_path in shell_write_targets(command):\n   177\t                rel = relative_path(root, raw_path)\n   178\t                if is_impl_path(rel):\n   179\t                    impl_shell_targets.append(rel)\n   180\t            if impl_shell_targets:\n   181\t                preview = \", \".join(sorted(set(impl_shell_targets))[:3])\n   182\t                return deny(\n   183\t                    \"SH-1: shell-write into src/erre_sandbox/ is forbidden; \"\n   184\t                    \"use Edit/Write/apply_patch tools so the same policy \"\n   185\t                    f\"guards apply. Detected target(s): {preview}\"\n   186\t                )\n   187\t    normalized = {\n   188\t        relative_path(root, path): lines for path, lines in target_map(payload).items()\n   189\t    }\n   190\t    if not normalized:\n   191\t        return 0\n   192\t    impl_targets = [path for path in normalized if is_impl_path(path)]\n   193\t    if impl_targets:\n   194\t        status = task_status(latest_task(root))\n   195\t        if status[\"task\"] is None:\n   196\t            return deny(\n   197\t                \"Implementation edits require a recent .steering/YYYYMMDD-task directory \"\n   198\t                \"with requirement.md, design.md, and tasklist.md.\"\n   199\t            )\n   200\t        if status[\"missing\"]:\n   201\t            return deny(\n   202\t                f\"Implementation edits require complete steering files; missing: \"\n   203\t                f\"{', '.join(status['missing'])}.\"\n   204\t            )\n   205\t    for path, lines in normalized.items():\n   206\t        violation = check_banned(path, lines)\n   207\t        if violation:\n   208\t            return deny(violation)\n   209\t    return 0\n   210\t\n   211\t\n   212\tif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   213\t    raise SystemExit(main())\n"}}
/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/15/rollout-2026-05-15T18-02-57-019e2adf-e667-7241-b4b7-edcb4561a395.jsonl:68:{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T09:04:00.408Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_f6dR93F5ZbnOS5s3H5ZugfNS","output":"Chunk ID: adf004\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 450\nOutput:\n     1\t{\n     2\t  \"hooks\": {\n     3\t    \"SessionStart\": [\n     4\t      {\n     5\t        \"matcher\": \"startup|resume|clear\",\n     6\t        \"hooks\": [\n     7\t          {\n     8\t            \"type\": \"command\",\n     9\t            \"command\": \"/usr/bin/python3 \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/.codex/hooks/session_start.py\\\"\",\n    10\t            \"timeout\": 10,\n    11\t            \"statusMessage\": \"Loading ERRE Codex context\"\n    12\t          }\n    13\t        ]\n    14\t      }\n    15\t    ],\n    16\t    \"UserPromptSubmit\": [\n    17\t      {\n    18\t        \"hooks\": [\n    19\t          {\n    20\t            \"type\": \"command\",\n    21\t            \"command\": \"/usr/bin/python3 \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/.codex/hooks/user_prompt_submit.py\\\"\",\n    22\t            \"timeout\": 10,\n    23\t            \"statusMessage\": \"Checking ERRE task context\"\n    24\t          }\n    25\t        ]\n    26\t      }\n    27\t    ],\n    28\t    \"PreToolUse\": [\n    29\t      {\n    30\t        \"matcher\": \"apply_patch|Edit|Write|exec_command|Bash\",\n    31\t        \"hooks\": [\n    32\t          {\n    33\t            \"type\": \"command\",\n    34\t            \"command\": \"/usr/bin/python3 \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/.codex/hooks/pre_tool_use_policy.py\\\"\",\n    35\t            \"timeout\": 10,\n    36\t            \"statusMessage\": \"Checking ERRE edit policy\"\n    37\t          }\n    38\t        ]\n    39\t      }\n    40\t    ],\n    41\t    \"Stop\": [\n    42\t      {\n    43\t        \"hooks\": [\n    44\t          {\n    45\t            \"type\": \"command\",\n    46\t            \"command\": \"/usr/bin/python3 \\\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/.codex/hooks/stop_report.py\\\"\",\n    47\t            \"timeout\": 60,\n    48\t            \"statusMessage\": \"Running ERRE stop checks\"\n    49\t          }\n    50\t        ]\n    51\t      }\n    52\t    ]\n    53\t  }\n    54\t}\n"}}
/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/15/rollout-2026-05-15T18-02-57-019e2adf-e667-7241-b4b7-edcb4561a395.jsonl:69:{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T09:04:00.408Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_NANI42enzo36bcxCCtom2LY3","output":"Chunk ID: f28e5f\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2084\nOutput:\n     1\t\"\"\"SH-1 red-team tests for the ``pre_tool_use_policy.py`` Codex hook.\n     2\t\n     3\tThe hook gates ``exec_command`` / ``Bash`` tool calls that would write into\n     4\t``src/erre_sandbox/`` via shell redirects, ``sed -i``, ``tee``, heredocs,\n     5\tor inline Python literals. Each case below invokes the hook as a fresh\n     6\tsubprocess with a synthetic Codex-style payload on stdin and asserts the\n     7\thook emits the JSON ``permissionDecision=\"deny\"`` envelope (the canonical\n     8\tCodex hook protocol; the helper-level ``deny()`` returns exit 0 with the\n     9\tstructured stdout so downstream telemetry stays parseable).\n    10\t\"\"\"\n    11\t\n    12\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n    13\t\n    14\timport json\n    15\timport subprocess\n    16\timport sys\n    17\tfrom pathlib import Path\n    18\tfrom typing import Any\n    19\t\n    20\timport pytest\n    21\t\n    22\tREPO_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2]\n    23\tHOOK_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \".codex\" / \"hooks\" / \"pre_tool_use_policy.py\"\n    24\t\n    25\t\n    26\tdef _invoke_hook(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    27\t    \"\"\"Run the hook as a fresh subprocess and parse its JSON stdout.\n    28\t\n    29\t    The hook contract is ``exit 0`` + JSON ``permissionDecision`` envelope\n    30\t    in stdout (Codex protocol). The subprocess is run with the project\n    31\t    repo root as CWD so ``repo_root`` / ``latest_task`` resolve to the\n    32\t    live ``.steering/`` tree and the SH-1 guard fires on its own merit\n    33\t    rather than via the ``.steering`` completeness fallback.\n    34\t    \"\"\"\n    35\t    result = subprocess.run(  # noqa: S603 — fixed argv to the in-repo hook\n    36\t        [sys.executable, str(HOOK_PATH)],\n    37\t        input=json.dumps(payload),\n    38\t        capture_output=True,\n    39\t        text=True,\n    40\t        timeout=10,\n    41\t        cwd=str(REPO_ROOT),\n    42\t        check=False,\n    43\t    )\n    44\t    assert result.returncode == 0, (\n    45\t        f\"hook returncode={result.returncode}\\n\"\n    46\t        f\"stderr={result.stderr}\\nstdout={result.stdout}\"\n    47\t    )\n    48\t    stdout = result.stdout.strip()\n    49\t    if not stdout:\n    50\t        # Allow path: ``main()`` returns 0 without writing to stdout when no\n    51\t        # rule fires. Tests checking benign commands should see this branch.\n    52\t        return {}\n    53\t    try:\n    54\t        return json.loads(stdout)\n    55\t    except json.JSONDecodeError as exc:  # pragma: no cover — diagnostic only\n    56\t        pytest.fail(f\"hook stdout not JSON: {stdout!r} (err={exc})\")\n    57\t\n    58\t\n    59\tdef _assert_deny(envelope: dict[str, Any], *, contains: str) -> None:\n    60\t    \"\"\"Helper: assert the hook envelope is a deny mentioning ``contains``.\"\"\"\n    61\t    hook_output = envelope.get(\"hookSpecificOutput\", {})\n    62\t    assert hook_output.get(\"permissionDecision\") == \"deny\", envelope\n    63\t    reason = hook_output.get(\"permissionDecisionReason\", \"\")\n    64\t    assert contains in reason, (\n    65\t        f\"expected deny reason to mention {contains!r}, got {reason!r}\"\n    66\t    )\n    67\t\n    68\t\n    69\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    70\t# Red-team: 5 canonical shell-write techniques the hook must block.\n    71\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    72\t\n    73\t\n    74\tdef test_sed_in_place_into_impl_is_denied() -> None:\n    75\t    \"\"\"``sed -i`` rewriting an impl file is denied (in-place edit bypass).\"\"\"\n    76\t    payload = {\n    77\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n    78\t        \"tool_input\": {\n    79\t            \"command\": (\n    80\t                \"sed -i 's/from typing/from typing\\\\nimport openai/' \"\n    81\t                \"src/erre_sandbox/inference/sglang_adapter.py\"\n    82\t            ),\n    83\t        },\n    84\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n    85\t    }\n    86\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n    87\t    _assert_deny(envelope, contains=\"SH-1\")\n    88\t\n    89\t\n    90\tdef test_echo_append_into_impl_is_denied() -> None:\n    91\t    \"\"\"``echo \"...\" >> PATH`` redirected into an impl file is denied.\"\"\"\n    92\t    payload = {\n    93\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n    94\t        \"tool_input\": {\n    95\t            \"command\": ('echo \"import bpy\" >> src/erre_sandbox/world/tick.py'),\n    96\t        },\n    97\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n    98\t    }\n    99\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   100\t    _assert_deny(envelope, contains=\"SH-1\")\n   101\t\n   102\t\n   103\tdef test_tee_into_impl_is_denied() -> None:\n   104\t    \"\"\"``tee PATH`` writing to an impl file is denied (even with empty stdin).\"\"\"\n   105\t    payload = {\n   106\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n   107\t        \"tool_input\": {\n   108\t            \"command\": \"tee src/erre_sandbox/x.py < /dev/null\",\n   109\t        },\n   110\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n   111\t    }\n   112\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   113\t    _assert_deny(envelope, contains=\"SH-1\")\n   114\t\n   115\t\n   116\tdef test_python_dash_c_open_write_into_impl_is_denied() -> None:\n   117\t    \"\"\"``python -c \"open(PATH, 'w').write(...)\"`` is denied.\"\"\"\n   118\t    payload = {\n   119\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n   120\t        \"tool_input\": {\n   121\t            \"command\": (\n   122\t                \"python -c \\\"open('src/erre_sandbox/y.py','w').write('print(1)')\\\"\"\n   123\t            ),\n   124\t        },\n   125\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n   126\t    }\n   127\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   128\t    _assert_deny(envelope, contains=\"SH-1\")\n   129\t\n   130\t\n   131\tdef test_cat_heredoc_into_impl_is_denied() -> None:\n   132\t    \"\"\"``cat > PATH << EOF ... EOF`` heredoc into an impl file is denied.\"\"\"\n   133\t    payload = {\n   134\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n   135\t        \"tool_input\": {\n   136\t            \"command\": (\"cat > src/erre_sandbox/z.py <<EOF\\nimport anthropic\\nEOF\"),\n   137\t        },\n   138\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n   139\t    }\n   140\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   141\t    _assert_deny(envelope, contains=\"SH-1\")\n   142\t\n   143\t\n   144\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   145\t# Negative path: benign shell commands must NOT be denied by the SH-1 gate.\n   146\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   147\t\n   148\t\n   149\tdef test_grep_into_impl_is_allowed() -> None:\n   150\t    \"\"\"Read-only ``grep src/erre_sandbox/...`` does not match write patterns.\"\"\"\n   151\t    payload = {\n   152\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n   153\t        \"tool_input\": {\n   154\t            \"command\": \"grep -rn 'WorldRuntime' src/erre_sandbox/world\",\n   155\t        },\n   156\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n   157\t    }\n   158\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   159\t    # No write into impl → empty target_map → main() returns 0 with empty\n   160\t    # stdout. JSON parse of an empty stdout raises — handle that fall-back.\n   161\t    hook_output = envelope.get(\"hookSpecificOutput\") if envelope else None\n   162\t    if hook_output is not None:\n   163\t        # If the hook emitted anything, it must NOT be a deny for SH-1.\n   164\t        decision = hook_output.get(\"permissionDecision\")\n   165\t        if decision == \"deny\":\n   166\t            reason = hook_output.get(\"permissionDecisionReason\", \"\")\n   167\t            assert \"SH-1\" not in reason, (\n   168\t                \"grep read-only command must not trip the SH-1 shell-write guard\"\n   169\t            )\n   170\t\n   171\t\n   172\tdef test_shell_write_outside_impl_is_allowed() -> None:\n   173\t    \"\"\"Writing to /tmp or var/ via shell is allowed (not in src/erre_sandbox/).\"\"\"\n   174\t    payload = {\n   175\t        \"tool\": \"exec_command\",\n   176\t        \"tool_input\": {\n   177\t            \"command\": 'echo \"junk\" > /tmp/scratch.txt',\n   178\t        },\n   179\t        \"cwd\": str(REPO_ROOT),\n   180\t    }\n   181\t    envelope = _invoke_hook(payload)\n   182\t    hook_output = envelope.get(\"hookSpecificOutput\") if envelope else None\n   183\t    if hook_output is not None:\n   184\t        decision = hook_output.get(\"permissionDecision\")\n   185\t        if decision == \"deny\":\n   186\t            reason = hook_output.get(\"permissionDecisionReason\", \"\")\n   187\t            assert \"SH-1\" not in reason, (\n   188\t                \"shell-write to /tmp must not trip the SH-1 src/erre_sandbox/ guard\"\n   189\t            )\n"}}
/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/15/rollout-2026-05-15T18-02-57-019e2adf-e667-7241-b4b7-edcb4561a395.jsonl:96:{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T09:04:27.715Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_dQTrV9Tl2CM9LXZhp4JxKHr4","output":"Chunk ID: af334f\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2540\nOutput:\n     1\t# 設計判断 — security-hardening-pre-m10-followup\n     2\t\n     3\t本 task は **親 task `.steering/20260513-security-hardening-pre-m10/decisions.md` の SH-1 / SH-2 ADR をそのまま実装する** ため、新 ADR を立てない。以下は親 ADR の verbatim 引用 (linkback 付き) + 開始時 fact-check の記録 + 本 task 中に発生した implementation-level 判断 (ADR addendum 形式)。\n     4\t\n     5\t---\n     6\t\n     7\t## SH-1 (親 task verbatim 引用) — Hook + CI shell-bypass defense\n     8\t\n     9\tSource: `.steering/20260513-security-hardening-pre-m10/decisions.md` SH-1\n    10\t\n    11\t- **判断日時**: 2026-05-13\n    12\t- **背景**: `codex_issue.md` §1 HIGH。`.codex/hooks.json:28-39` matcher が `apply_patch|Edit|Write` のみ、`exec_command` 経由の shell 書き込みが `.steering` completeness guard / banned import check を通過する。\n    13\t- **選択肢**:\n    14\t  - A: hook matcher 拡張のみ (`exec_command|Bash` 追加)\n    15\t  - B: CI grep gate 追加のみ (`policy-grep-gate` job)\n    16\t  - **C**: hook + CI の両層\n    17\t- **採用**: **C**\n    18\t- **理由**:\n    19\t  - hook 単独 (A) は `apply_patch` 偽装で素通り、bypass risk が残る\n    20\t  - CI 単独 (B) は feedback latency が遅い (PR push 後)、IDE 内即時 deny の UX を失う\n    21\t  - 両層 (C) は既存 `eval-egress-grep-gate` (`ci.yml:83-137`) が同型パターンとして validated、defense-in-depth 完成\n    22\t- **トレードオフ**: 開発時の hook 誤検知 (false positive) リスク増。red-team test 5 ケースで pattern 妥当性を担保\n    23\t- **影響範囲**: `.codex/hooks/` + `.github/workflows/ci.yml` + 新規 `tests/test_codex_hooks/`\n    24\t- **見直しタイミング**: red-team test で誤検知率 >5% に達した場合、または CI grep gate が M9-eval / m9-c-spike 系の正当なツール使用をブロックした場合\n    25\t\n    26\t---\n    27\t\n    28\t## SH-2 (親 task verbatim 引用) — WebSocket 3-layer auth (token + Origin + cap)\n    29\t\n    30\tSource: `.steering/20260513-security-hardening-pre-m10/decisions.md` SH-2\n    31\t\n    32\t- **判断日時**: 2026-05-13\n    33\t- **背景**: `codex_issue.md` §2 MEDIUM。`__main__.py:73-74` / `bootstrap.py:70-71` default `0.0.0.0:8000`、`integration/gateway.py:501-652` `ws_observe()` に認証 / Origin / session cap いずれもなし。Mac↔G-GEAR LAN rsync workflow は LAN 内前提だが、共有 Wi-Fi 誤公開時の blast radius が無制限。\n    34\t- **選択肢** (Plan agent enumeration + AskUserQuestion):\n    35\t  - **A. Token rollout: back-compat 優先** (`require_token=False` default、Godot patch を別 PR、enforce は後続)\n    36\t  - B. Token rollout: 同一 PR 強制 (P4 で Godot WS client patch も含める)\n    37\t  - C. Token rollout: Godot 免除 list (loopback の Godot は token 不要)\n    38\t- **採用**: **A** (ユーザー選択、2026-05-13 AskUserQuestion)\n    39\t- **理由**:\n    40\t  - A は blast radius 最小 (Godot 未パッチでも continue)、PR 単位の独立性高い\n    41\t  - B は Godot patch を blocker 化、本 PR scope 拡大 + Godot live test 必要で工数 +5h\n    42\t  - C は認証ロジック分岐増、SH-2 の \"3 layer independent\" 原則を破る\n    43\t- **トレードオフ**: A 採用で token 機構は **存在するが強制しない** 初期状態、別 PR で `require_token=True` default 化が必要。記録: `tasklist.md` に follow-up task 起票\n    44\t- **追加判断**:\n    45\t  - **`MAX_ACTIVE_SESSIONS = 8`** (Mac+G-GEAR Godot + curl + slack + M10 per-persona UI × 3、4 では tight、16 は memory waste で却下、AskUserQuestion 結果)\n    46\t  - **Token storage**: file `var/secrets/ws_token` primary + env `ERRE_WS_TOKEN` fallback + explicit `--ws-token` arg は test のみ (`ps -E` leak 回避)\n    47\t  - **Origin allowlist**: 空 list ⇒ check disabled (Godot native WS empty Origin 対応)、`host=0.0.0.0` + empty origin + `require_token=False` は startup error で誤公開予防\n    48\t- **棄却**:\n    49\t  - mTLS (運用負荷過大、cert rotate 必要)\n    50\t  - cookie auth (Godot native WS が cookie 非対応)\n    51\t  - `127.0.0.1` 強制 (Mac↔G-GEAR LAN rsync workflow 実害)\n    52\t- **影響範囲**: `__main__.py` / `bootstrap.py` / `integration/gateway.py` / `integration/protocol.py` / `docs/architecture.md` / `README.md` / `docs/development-guidelines.md` / `tests/test_integration/test_gateway.py`\n    53\t- **見直しタイミング**:\n    54\t  - Godot 4.4 WS client が token 対応した時点で `require_token=True` default 化の follow-up PR\n    55\t  - `MAX_ACTIVE_SESSIONS=8` が M11 で不足判明した場合、cap 値 reopen\n    56\t  - LAN 外公開要件が発生した場合 (M14+? OSF 公開時)、mTLS 検討\n    57\t\n    58\t---\n    59\t\n    60\t## SH-FOLLOWUP-1 — `deny()` exit code 解釈の確定\n    61\t\n    62\t- **判断日時**: 2026-05-15 (本 task 開始時 fact-check)\n    63\t- **背景**: 起点プロンプト `.steering/20260513-security-hardening-pre-m10/next-session-prompt-followup.md` Step 3 の hook smoke 検証で「exit 2 + deny message」を期待していたが、実機 `pre_tool_use_policy.py:37` の `deny()` は **exit 0 + JSON `permissionDecision:\"deny\"`** を返す (Codex 公式 hook protocol)。\n    64\t- **選択肢** (AskUserQuestion):\n    65\t  - **A**: JSON deny を維持、smoke 検証を JSON match に修正 (Recommended、ユーザー採用)\n    66\t  - B: `deny()` を return 2 に変更 + JSON も併用\n    67\t  - C: プロンプト通り exit 2 のみ (JSON 廃止)\n    68\t- **採用**: **A**\n    69\t- **理由**:\n    70\t  - 現実装は Codex 公式 `permissionDecision: \"deny\"` JSON 構造を採用、reason 文字列が structured で telemetry 親和性が高い\n    71\t  - B は二重化だが既存 `deny()` 呼出箇所 (4 箇所) の挙動は実用上変わらず、変更 cost に見合わない\n    72\t  - C は structured reason を捨てる退行\n    73\t- **トレードオフ**: hook smoke 検証手順がプロンプト本文と異なる (`jq -e '.hookSpecificOutput.permissionDecision == \"deny\"'`)。本 ADR で記録、Codex 14th review prompt にも明記\n    74\t- **影響範囲**: `tests/test_codex_hooks/test_shell_bypass_policy.py` の assert は stdout JSON match、`.steering/20260513-security-hardening-pre-m10/next-session-prompt-followup.md` Step 3 hook smoke 行は本 task 後 stale 化 (修正不要、`git rm next-session-prompt.md` 同梱で発生する `next-session-prompt-followup.md` も同様に close 時に処理判定)\n    75\t- **見直しタイミング**: Codex CLI の hook protocol が future version で exit code based に強制移行した場合\n    76\t\n    77\t---\n    78\t\n    79\t## SH-FOLLOWUP-2 — CI policy-grep-gate の T201 backstop 設計\n    80\t\n    81\t- **判断日時**: 2026-05-15 (本 task 開始時 fact-check)\n    82\t- **背景**: 親 task design-final.md L67 で `grep -rnE '^\\s*print\\s*\\(' src/erre_sandbox/` を T201 backstop として設計していたが、Bash fact-check で `src/erre_sandbox/inference/ollama_adapter.py:145` に既存の **noqa なし raw print()** が存在することが判明。CI は現状 green なので ruff 側に何らかの allow 経路がある (file-level skip or pyproject extra exemption の可能性)。\n    83\t- **選択肢** (AskUserQuestion):\n    84\t  - **A**: ruff と同等の例外 (cli/** 除外 + 行 noqa 尊重) — `uv run ruff check --select T201 src/erre_sandbox` 再実行で代替 (Recommended、ユーザー採用)\n    85\t  - B: 厳格 grep で全 print() を block (既存 `ollama_adapter.py:145` も対象、本 PR で `# noqa: T201` 追加か `logger.debug` 置換必要)\n    86\t  - C: print rule は CI grep から外す、import 禁止と `.steering` completeness のみ grep\n    87\t- **採用**: **A**\n    88\t- **理由**:\n    89\t  - 既存 CI green を破壊しない (retro-active breakage なし)\n    90\t  - ruff exemption は pyproject + per-line noqa で集約管理、CI grep で重複 enforce すると drift risk\n    91\t  - SH-1 design-final.md L67 「ruff T201 の backstop」要件は、grep ではなく ruff 自身の冪等再実行でも満たされる (CI 内別 job で実行 = backstop)\n    92\t- **トレードオフ**: 厳格 grep より弱い (\"ruff 自身の bug\" が backstop で検出できない)。ruff version pin と CI step 順序で品質保証\n    93\t- **影響範囲**: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` `policy-grep-gate` job の print step は `uv run ruff check --select T201 src/erre_sandbox` に。grep は openai/anthropic + bpy + `.steering` completeness のみ\n    94\t- **見直しタイミング**: ruff `T201` が future version で削除 / rename された場合、または `ollama_adapter.py:145` を本来正しく block すべき判断が後日発生した場合 (別 task で audit)\n    95\t\n    96\t---\n    97\t\n    98\t## SH-FOLLOWUP-3 — (placeholder)\n    99\t\n   100\tCodex 14th review で MEDIUM 切出時にここに ADR addendum を追加する。\n   101\t\n   102\t---\n   103\t\n   104\t## Mac↔G-GEAR LAN smoke 手順 (P4d 必須、SH-2 ADR の見直しタイミングに関連)\n   105\t\n   106\t`require_token=False` default で既存 rsync workflow が不変であることを実機で確認:\n   107\t\n   108\t```bash\n   109\t# Mac 側 (本 PR の branch)\n   110\tuv run python -m erre_sandbox --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 \\\n   111\t  --personas study/peripatos --check-ollama false &\n   112\tSERVER_PID=$!\n   113\tsleep 3\n   114\t\n   115\t# G-GEAR 側 (curl で WS handshake without token)\n   116\tcurl -i -N \\\n   117\t  -H \"Connection: Upgrade\" -H \"Upgrade: websocket\" \\\n   118\t  -H \"Sec-WebSocket-Key: dGhlIHNhbXBsZSBub25jZQ==\" \\\n   119\t  -H \"Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13\" \\\n   120\t  http://mac.local:8000/observe\n   121\t# Expected: 101 Switching Protocols (require_token=False なので token 不要)\n   122\t\n   123\tkill $SERVER_PID\n   124\t```\n   125\t\n   126\t本 smoke は手動。`tests/test_integration/test_gateway.py::TestWebSocketAuth::test_back_compat_no_token_required_by_default` で代替自動化済 (single-host TestClient 経由)。\n"}}
