算チェック (`per_invocation_max` 未満なら exit 1)\n2. `secrets-filter.sh` を通して exit code 2 なら中止\n3. proprietary 拡張子混入の grep\n4. ユーザー preview 表示 (`--preview` フラグで送信前確認可)\n\n### Step 3: wrapper 経由で Codex 呼び出し\n\n```bash\nscripts/run-codex-consult.sh /tmp/codex-consult-input.md\n```\n\nwrapper 内部で以下のプロンプトで Codex に投げる:\n\n> 以下の設計案について、独立した視点から:\n> 1. 抜けている観点 (主要な落とし穴、エッジケース)\n> 2. 候補案 A/B/C 以外に検討すべき選択肢\n> 3. 採用案のリスクと、軽減策の追加アイデア\n> 4. トレードオフ評価で見落としがちな点\n>\n> 400 語以内、優先度順に。日本語可。「採用案を支持/不支持」ではなく **盲点指摘 + 追加アイデア** に専念する。\n\n## 出力の取り扱い\n\nCodex の応答を受け取った Codex は以下の方針で統合:\n\n- Codex の指摘で **明らかな盲点** だったものは、設計案を修正\n- **既知のトレードオフ** だったものは、判断理由を強化して書き残す\n- **誤検知 / 文脈理解不足** だった指摘は、却下理由を記録 (Codex には文脈の半分しか渡していないので false positive は起こる)\n- ユーザーに「Codex はこういう指摘もしてきた」と提示し、最終判断を仰ぐ\n\n## 関連 Skill / ファイル\n\n- `codex-review` — 実装後の diff レビュー (こちらは設計後)\n- `codex-rescue` — 詰まった実装の委譲 (こちらは実装中)\n- `.codex/config.toml`, `.codex/budget.json` — 予算管理\n- `scripts/run-codex-consult.sh` — 本 Skill 専用 wrapper\n- `scripts/secrets-filter.sh` — 機密フィルタ\n\n## アンチパターン\n\n- ❌ 設計ドキュメント全文を生で送る (公開可能な最小抜粋に絞ること)\n- ❌ プロジェクト固有の internal 名称を仮名化せずに送る\n- ❌ Codex の指摘を盲信して設計を変える (Codex は文脈の半分しか持っていない)\n- ❌ 既に実装が始まったタスクで本 Skill を使う (codex-review / codex-rescue の領域)\n- ❌ 軽量な設計判断で毎回呼ぶ (token コスト爆発、predicate を「Codex が不安な時のみ」に保つ)\n- ❌ ユーザー preview なしに送信する (wrapper の `--preview` フラグで承認制)\n"}}
.steering/20260515-security-hardening-pre-m10-followup/codex-review.stderr:6072:/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/11/rollout-2026-05-11T21-06-25-019e16ee-7034-77b2-81d2-b2dbf1e45a6a.jsonl:105:{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T12:08:37.190Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_fWMZQSdYqov0CEuKvVvhrKku","output":"Chunk ID: fe2439\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1282\nOutput:\n     1\t#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     3\t\n     4\timport re\n     5\tfrom pathlib import Path\n     6\tfrom typing import Any\n     7\t\n     8\tfrom _erre_common import emit_json, latest_task, read_payload, relative_path, repo_root, task_status\n     9\t\n    10\tIMPL_PREFIX = \"src/erre_sandbox/\"\n    11\tBANNED_PATTERNS: list[tuple[str, re.Pattern[str]]] = [\n    12\t    (\n    13\t        \"cloud LLM API imports are forbidden in src/erre_sandbox\",\n    14\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*(?:import\\s+(?:openai|anthropic)\\b|from\\s+(?:openai|anthropic)\\b)\"),\n    15\t    ),\n    16\t    (\n    17\t        \"bpy imports are forbidden in src/erre_sandbox because Blender/GPL code is isolated\",\n    18\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*(?:import\\s+bpy\\b|from\\s+bpy\\b)\"),\n    19\t    ),\n    20\t    (\n    21\t        \"print() is forbidden in src/erre_sandbox; use logging instead\",\n    22\t        re.compile(r\"^\\s*print\\s*\\(\"),\n    23\t    ),\n    24\t]\n    25\t\n    26\t\n    27\tdef deny(reason: str) -> int:\n    28\t    emit_json(\n    29\t        {\n    30\t            \"hookSpecificOutput\": {\n    31\t                \"hookEventName\": \"PreToolUse\",\n    32\t                \"permissionDecision\": \"deny\",\n    33\t                \"permissionDecisionReason\": reason,\n    34\t            }\n    35\t        }\n    36\t    )\n    37\t    return 0\n    38\t\n    39\t\n    40\tdef patch_targets(command: str) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n    41\t    targets: dict[str, list[str]] = {}\n    42\t    current: str | None = None\n    43\t    for line in command.splitlines():\n    44\t        for marker in (\"*** Add File: \", \"*** Update File: \", \"*** Delete File: \"):\n    45\t            if line.startswith(marker):\n    46\t                current = line[len(marker) :].strip()\n    47\t                targets.setdefault(current, [])\n    48\t                break\n    49\t        else:\n    50\t            if current and line.startswith(\"+\") and not line.startswith(\"+++\"):\n    51\t                targets[current].append(line[1:])\n    52\t    return targets\n    53\t\n    54\t\n    55\tdef direct_targets(tool_input: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n    56\t    result: dict[str, list[str]] = {}\n    57\t    for key in (\"file_path\", \"path\"):\n    58\t        value = tool_input.get(key)\n    59\t        if isinstance(value, str) and value:\n    60\t            content = tool_input.get(\"new_string\") or tool_input.get(\"content\") or \"\"\n    61\t            if isinstance(content, str):\n    62\t                result[value] = content.splitlines()\n    63\t    edits = tool_input.get(\"edits\")\n    64\t    target = tool_input.get(\"file_path\") or tool_input.get(\"path\")\n    65\t    if isinstance(edits, list) and isinstance(target, str):\n    66\t        lines: list[str] = []\n    67\t        for edit in edits:\n    68\t            if isinstance(edit, dict) and isinstance(edit.get(\"new_string\"), str):\n    69\t                lines.extend(edit[\"new_string\"].splitlines())\n    70\t        result[target] = lines\n    71\t    return result\n    72\t\n    73\t\n    74\tdef target_map(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n    75\t    tool_input = payload.get(\"tool_input\")\n    76\t    if not isinstance(tool_input, dict):\n    77\t        return {}\n    78\t    command = tool_input.get(\"command\")\n    79\t    if isinstance(command, str) and \"*** Begin Patch\" in command:\n    80\t        return patch_targets(command)\n    81\t    return direct_targets(tool_input)\n    82\t\n    83\t\n    84\tdef is_impl_path(path: str) -> bool:\n    85\t    return path.startswith(IMPL_PREFIX)\n    86\t\n    87\t\n    88\tdef check_banned(path: str, lines: list[str]) -> str | None:\n    89\t    if not path.endswith(\".py\") or not is_impl_path(path):\n    90\t        return None\n    91\t    for line in lines:\n    92\t        for label, pattern in BANNED_PATTERNS:\n    93\t            if pattern.search(line):\n    94\t                return f\"{label}: {path}: {line.strip()}\"\n    95\t    return None\n    96\t\n    97\t\n    98\tdef main() -> int:\n    99\t    payload = read_payload()\n   100\t    root = repo_root(payload)\n   101\t    normalized = {\n   102\t        relative_path(root, path): lines for path, lines in target_map(payload).items()\n   103\t    }\n   104\t    if not normalized:\n   105\t        return 0\n   106\t    impl_targets = [path for path in normalized if is_impl_path(path)]\n   107\t    if impl_targets:\n   108\t        status = task_status(latest_task(root))\n   109\t        if status[\"task\"] is None:\n   110\t            return deny(\n   111\t                \"Implementation edits require a recent .steering/YYYYMMDD-task directory \"\n   112\t                \"with requirement.md, design.md, and tasklist.md.\"\n   113\t            )\n   114\t        if status[\"missing\"]:\n   115\t            return deny(\n   116\t                f\"Implementation edits require complete steering files; missing: \"\n   117\t                f\"{', '.join(status['missing'])}.\"\n   118\t            )\n   119\t    for path, lines in normalized.items():\n   120\t        violation = check_banned(path, lines)\n   121\t        if violation:\n   122\t            return deny(violation)\n   123\t    return 0\n   124\t\n   125\t\n   126\tif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   127\t    raise SystemExit(main())\n"}}
