UT_MIN`: 90.0 → 120.0\n   357\t    - [x] test rewrite 2 件 (`test_eval_natural_mode_uses_reduced_cooldown` /\n   358\t          `test_eval_natural_mode_sustains_admission_after_initial_burst`) +\n   359\t          新規 4 件 (`test_effective_cooldown_returns_eval_value_when_flag_true` /\n   360\t          `test_effective_cooldown_returns_live_value_when_flag_false` /\n   361\t          `test_live_mode_cooldown_unchanged_via_tick` / \n   362\t          `test_wall_timeout_min_default_is_120`) 全 PASS\n   363\t    - [x] full suite **1251 passed** / 31 skipped / 27 deselected (baseline 1248 から\n   364\t          default CI に +3、CLI test 1 件は eval marker で deselect)\n   365\t    - [x] `decisions.md` ME-8 amendment 2026-05-01 ブロック追加 (二度目の partial\n   366\t          update、explicit amendment with PR #131 empirical data)\n   367\t    - [x] `g-gear-p3a-rerun-prompt-v2.md` 起草 (Phase A 期待値桁再校正、wall 120 min)\n   368\t    - [x] `.codex/budget.json` 145,717 tokens 記録 (per_invocation_max=200K 内)\n   369\t  - [ ] **next G-GEAR セッション v2** (rerun-prompt-v2.md を貼り付けて起動):\n   370\t    - [ ] fix v2 適用版 (`COOLDOWN_TICKS_EVAL=5` + wall default 120) で natural\n   371\t          3 cell 再々採取 (focal>=25 target、Phase A 単独 sanity → Phase B 3 並列)\n   372\t    - [ ] DuckDB rsync via `/tmp/p3a_rsync_v2/` snapshot + ME-2 protocol\n   373\t  - [ ] **next Mac セッション** (rsync 完了後):\n   374\t    - [ ] `uv run python scripts/p3a_decide.py` で両 condition の CI 計算\n   375\t    - [ ] Burrows Delta / Vendi / Big5 ICC の CI width 比較\n   376\t    - [ ] ME-4 ADR を **二度目の Edit** で実測値 ratio 確定 (200/300 default vs\n   377\t          alternative)\n   378\t    - [ ] M9-B `blockers.md` の \"Hybrid baseline 比率 200/300\" 項目を close\n   379\t          (現状 M9-B blockers.md には該当項目なし。本セッションでは追加せず、\n   380\t          ratio 確定時に M9-B 側へ通知 / 必要なら起票)\n"}}
.steering/20260515-security-hardening-pre-m10-followup/codex-review.stderr:6098:/Users/johnd/.codex/sessions/2026/05/12/rollout-2026-05-12T14-41-27-019e1ab4-5ae2-7093-a76b-4cf0adc1dd46.jsonl:182:{"timestamp":"2026-05-12T05:55:31.584Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_JwwNRhRMXAdpmYBsuYF0xax6","output":"Chunk ID: 8b991d\nWall time: 30.0023 seconds\nProcess running with session ID 89882\nOriginal token count: 4372\nOutput:\nReading additional input from stdin...\nOpenAI Codex v0.125.0 (research preview)\n--------\nworkdir: /Users/johnd/cognitive-State Diary generator\nmodel: gpt-5.5\nprovider: openai\napproval: never\nsandbox: read-only\nreasoning effort: low\nreasoning summaries: none\nsession id: 019e1ac0-c7f4-7a30-b76e-95fd34b7a94e\n--------\nuser\nArchitecture/product judgement request for a Python LLM text-generation CLI. Current capabilities: sequential state-update/content-generation/critic pipeline; Pydantic state; two-layer memory; deterministic quality constraints; Anthropic/Gemini clients; SQLite cache; local Ollama model available qwen3:8b Q4_K_M. Proposed extensions: world model, richer human persona texture, Ollama local LLM support, multi-character, dynamic scenario, UI, streaming, eval harness. Please strictly rank which are worth doing now vs later vs not yet, with risks and minimal first slice. Do not assume private files.\n2026-05-12T05:55:02.523986Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: prompt must be at most 128 characters path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/build-ios-apps/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:02.526353Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/plugin-eval/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:02.546869Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/twilio-developer-kit/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:02.547058Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/openai-developers/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:03.774133Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: prompt must be at most 128 characters path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/build-ios-apps/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:03.774485Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/plugin-eval/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:03.777257Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/twilio-developer-kit/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:03.777306Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/openai-developers/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\nhook: SessionStart\nhook: SessionStart Completed\nhook: UserPromptSubmit\nhook: UserPromptSubmit Failed\n2026-05-12T05:55:05.167815Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: prompt must be at most 128 characters path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/build-ios-apps/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:05.168367Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/plugin-eval/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:05.170098Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/twilio-developer-kit/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:05.170129Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/openai-developers/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\ncodex\nI’ll use the `codex-consult` guidance because this is an architecture/product sequencing judgment, but I’ll keep the answer self-contained and avoid relying on repo-private files.\nhook: PreToolUse\nhook: PreToolUse\nhook: PreToolUse Completed\nhook: PreToolUse Completed\nexec\n/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' '/Users/johnd/cognitive-State Diary generator/.agents/skills/codex-consult/SKILL.md'\" in /Users/johnd/cognitive-State Diary generator\n succeeded in 0ms:\n---\nname: codex-consult\ndescription: >\n  Codex CLI (gpt-5.5) を独立した設計相談相手として呼び出すための Skill。\n  以下の状況で必須参照: 設計判断に迷った時、Codex 単独では視野が偏る恐れがある時、\n  アーキテクチャの選択肢を比較したい時、複雑なバグの原因仮説を独立に検証したい時。\n  read-only sandbox + low reasoning_effort で軽量に運用する。\n  diff レビュー (codex-review) や rescue 実装 (codex-rescue) とは責務を分離する。\nallowed-tools: Bash(scripts/run-codex-consult.sh:*), Read\n---\n\n# codex-consult — Codex を設計相談相手として使う\n\n## このSkillが対象とするケース\n\n- 「この設計でよいか」を Codex 単独で判断する前に、独立した第二意見が欲しい\n- アーキテクチャの選択肢が 2-3 個あり、トレードオフを言語化したい\n- 複雑なバグについて、Codex が立てた仮説を別の角度から検証したい\n- プロンプトの構造設計を相談したい (CSDG では Actor/Critic 設計の見直しなど)\n\n**対象外**: コード実装の依頼 (→ Codex 自身が書く / どうしても外部に頼みたいなら codex-rescue)、diff レビュー (→ codex-review)。\n\n## 入力の制約 (重要)\n\nCodex は **OpenAI の gpt-5.5 にプロンプトを送信する外部 LLM** であり、本プロジェクトの全ファイルを送るのは情報漏洩リスクがある。**送信内容は公開可能な最小抜粋に限定する**:\n\n- ✅ 抽象的な設計の質問 (\"Pydantic で discriminated union を扱うとき、validator のチェーン順序はどうあるべきか\")\n- ✅ 公開可能なコードスニペット (10-30 行程度)\n- ✅ 一般的なパターン名・ライブラリ名\n- ❌ API キー / 環境変数 / .env 内容\n- ❌ プロジェクト固有のプロンプト全文 (`prompts/*.md`)\n- ❌ ユーザーデータ・キャラクターペルソナの詳細\n- ❌ proprietary 拡張子のファイル (`.pdf`, `.docx`, `.xlsx`, `.pptx`)\n\n`scripts/run-codex-consult.sh` 内の `secrets-filter.sh` で機密パターン (API キー / private key / proprietary 拡張子) は自動 deny されるが、**フィルタは最終防衛線であり、入力時点で適切な抜粋を選ぶのが本来の責務**。\n\n## 使い方\n\n```bash\n# 最小例 (引数渡し)\nscripts/run-codex-consult.sh \"Pydantic v2 で複数の field_validator がある時、実行順序の保証は?\"\n\n# stdin 経由 (長文)\ncat <<'EOF' | scripts/run-codex-consult.sh\n[抽象化された質問 + 公開可能スニペット]\nEOF\n```\n\n## 出力の扱い\n\nCodex の応答は **第二意見として参照する** が、以下を遵守:\n- 応答内容を盲目的にコピペしない (バイアス・古い情報・本プロジェクト固有制約への無知の可能性)\n- Codex 自身が再評価し、本プロジェクトの規約 (development-guidelines.md) と照合してから実装に反映\n- 重要な設計判断は `.steering/[task]/decisions.md` に「Codex の意見も参照した」と明記\n\n## 予算管理\n\n`.codex/budget.json` の `daily_token_budget` (200000 token) を超えると wrapper が exit 3。\n1 回あたりの目安: 500-3000 token (low reasoning なので軽い)。\n\n## アンチパターン\n\n- ❌ 「とりあえず Codex に聞く」 — Codex が最低 1 案考えてから比較相談に使う\n- ❌ ファイル全文をそのまま流し込む — 抜粋する\n- ❌ 機密情報・ユーザーデータを送る\n- ❌ 同じ質問を再投する — 1 回の応答で十分なことが多い (予算節約)\n\n## 関連 Skill\n\n- `codex-review`: 完成した diff の独立レビュー (medium reasoning)\n- `codex-rescue`: Codex が詰まった時の代替実装 (workspace-write + worktree 隔離)\n\n2026-05-12T05:55:09.386504Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: prompt must be at most 128 characters path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/build-ios-apps/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:09.386772Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/plugin-eval/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:09.389176Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/twilio-developer-kit/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:09.389253Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/openai-developers/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\ncodex\nI’m going to get one lightweight independent pass on the ranking using only the abstract capability list you provided, then I’ll synthesize it rather than forwarding the output raw.\nhook: PreToolUse\nhook: PreToolUse\nhook: PreToolUse Completed\nhook: PreToolUse Completed\nexec\n/bin/zsh -lc \"scripts/run-codex-consult.sh 'Architecture/product judgement request for a Python LLM text-generation CLI. Current capabilities: sequential state-update/content-generation/critic pipeline; Pydantic state; two-layer memory; deterministic quality constraints; Anthropic/Gemini clients; SQLite cache; local Ollama model available qwen3:8b Q4_K_M. Proposed extensions: world model, richer human persona texture, Ollama local LLM support, multi-character, dynamic scenario, UI, streaming, eval harness. Strictly rank worth doing now vs later vs not yet, with risks and minimal first slice. No private files available. Provide concise product/architecture sequencing.'\" in /Users/johnd/cognitive-State Diary generator\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.565584Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: prompt must be at most 128 characters path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/build-ios-apps/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.566408Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/plugin-eval/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.569205Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/twilio-developer-kit/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.569251Z  WARN codex_core_plugins::manifest: ignoring interface.defaultPrompt: maximum of 3 prompts is supported path=/Users/johnd/.codex/.tmp/plugins/plugins/openai-developers/.codex-plugin/plugin.json\n exited 1 in 327ms:\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.337638Z  WARN codex_state::runtime: failed to open state db at /Users/johnd/.codex/state_5.sqlite: error returned from database: (code: 8) attempt to write a readonly database\n2026-05-12T05:55:15.337857Z  WARN codex_rollout::state_db: failed to initialize state runtime at /Users/johnd/.codex: error returned from database: 